{"type":"message","id":"45f9610b","parentId":"f528aec0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:14:01.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the most recent pulse log.","thinkingSignature":"d40b955382637849e2941533c26915d89f981b4c20bbf1dbf0828e4e565360b3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_afjcz6mcz35h_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 190347.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_afjcz6mcz35h_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"keen-meadow","timeout":60000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":452,"output":106,"cacheRead":11887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307638465}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb8f0437","parentId":"45f9610b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:14:01.687Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_afjcz6mcz35h_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 190347\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and the next action needed.\r\n\r\nThe current goal is to advance Phase 1 with the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The pending actions are:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI need to create a concrete file edit that advances this. The most immediate next step would be to:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier script or implementation plan\r\n2. Or create documentation/spec for the TIC experiment\r\n3. Or implement the classifier itself\r\n\r\nLet me create a practical implementation. Given the PowerShell environment, I should create a PowerShell script for the TIC classifier that can:\r\n1. Read pulse logs\r\n2. Classify content as invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (changes between pulses)\r\n3. Measure accuracy\r\n4. Predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me write a concrete implementation file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment needs a concrete implementation. The hypothesis is that causal structure equals invariant structure, so I need to build a classifier that distinguishes invariants from variants across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier PowerShell script that reads pulse logs, identifies invariant content (goals, architecture docs, etc.) vs variant content (timestamps, new insights, etc.), and measures classification accuracy against manually tagged examples.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [string]$TestSet = \"logs/test_set.md\",\r\n    [float]$Lambda = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- INVARIANT PATTERNS ---\r\n$InvariantPatterns = @(\r\n    \"Phase [0-9]\",\r\n    \"COMPLETE|PENDING|Active\",\r\n    \"Goals:|ARCHITECTURE|COMPRESSION-CAUSA\",\r\n    \"\\.md$\",\r\n    \"^## \",\r\n    \"research/\",\r\n    \"Last updated\",\r\n    \"Breakaway is stateless\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# --- VARIANT PATTERNS ---\r\n$VariantPatterns = @(\r\n    \"^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\",\r\n    \"pulse_[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\",\r\n    \"\\d{6}\\.md\",\r\n    \"Last pulse\",\r\n    \"Observation|Action|Mutation\",\r\n    \"No mutations applied\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunction Get-LineType {\r\n    param([string]$Line)\r\n    \r\n    $invScore = 0\r\n    $varScore = 0\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pat in $InvariantPatterns) {\r\n        if ($Line -match $pat) { $invScore += 1 }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($pat in $VariantPatterns) {\r\n        if ($Line -match $pat) { $varScore += 1 }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    if ($invScore -gt $varScore) { return \"INVARIANT\" }\r\n    if ($varScore -gt $invScore) { return \"VARIANT\" }\r\n    return \"NEUTRAL\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Test-TICClassifier {\r\n    Write-Host \"=== TIC Classifier Test ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n    Write-Host \"Lambda threshold: $Lambda\"\r\n    Write-Host \"\"\r\n    \r\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem \"logs/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime\r\n    Write-Host \"Found $($logs.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n    \r\n    if ($logs.Count -lt 2) {\r\n        Write-Host \"ERROR: Need at least 2 pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n        return\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Analyze invariant ratio across logs\r\n    $invariantCount = 0\r\n    $totalLines = 0\r\n    $invariantLines = @()\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($log in $logs) {\r\n        $lines = Get-Content $log.FullName\r\n        foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n            $totalLines++\r\n            $type = Get-LineType $line\r\n            if ($type -eq \"INVARIANT\") {\r\n                $invariantCount++\r\n                $invariantLines += $line\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $invariantRatio = if ($totalLines -gt 0) { $invariantCount / $totalLines } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    Write-Host \"Total lines analyzed: $totalLines\"\r\n    Write-Host \"Classified as INVARIANT: $invariantCount ($([math]::Round($invariantRatio * 100, 1))%)\"\r\n    Write-Host \"\"\r\n    \r\n    # Predict next pulse from invariants\r\n    Write-Host \"=== Next Pulse Prediction ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n    $uniqueInvariants = $invariantLines | Sort-Object -Unique\r\n    Write-Host \"Unique invariant lines for prediction: $($uniqueInvariants.Count)\"\r\n    \r\n    # Test: Check if last log's invariants match prediction\r\n    $lastLog = $logs[-1]\r\n    $lastLines = Get-Content $lastLog.FullName\r\n    $lastInvariants = $lastLines | Where-Object { (Get-LineType $_) -eq \"INVARIANT\" }\r\n    \r\n    $matchCount = 0\r\n    foreach ($inv in $lastInvariants) {\r\n        if ($uniqueInvariants -contains $inv) { $matchCount++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $predictionAccuracy = if ($lastInvariants.Count -gt 0) { $matchCount / $lastInvariants.Count } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    Write-Host \"Last log invariant match: $matchCount / $($lastInvariants.Count\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 19:04:17\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307641686}}
